HEADWORD: Elbowroom
<hw>El"bow*room`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Room to extend
the elbows on each side; ample room for motion or action; free
scope.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧My soul hath <xex>elbowroom</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then came a stretch of grass and a little more
<qex>elbowroom</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>W. G. Norris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

